label.value: decreased protein transport along microtubule to cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules to the cell tip is decreased. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein transport along microtubule to cell tip cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport to the cortex of the cell tip, driven by polymerization of a microtubule to which the protein is attached, is decreased. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein transport along microtubule during vegetative growth

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the transport of proteins along microtubules does not occur. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

label.value: abolished protein transport along microtubule to cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules to the cell tip does not occur. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein transport along microtubule to cell tip cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules to the cortex of the cell tip does not occur. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: symmetric mitochondrial aggregation

value.value: An abnormal intracellular mitochondrion distribution phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondria cluster together more than normal with a cluster distal to each side of the nucleus.

label.value: increased rate of medial membrane band assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of medial membrane band assembly is increased. Medial membrane band assembly is the assembly of a sterol-rich region of the plasma membrane at the cell surface overlying the contractile ring.

label.value: incomplete, asymmetric septum

value.value: A septation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms a septum that does not have uniform thickness and does not extend over the entire cell division site.

label.value: normal protein transport along microtubule to cell tip cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules to the cortex of the cell tip is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to interphase microtubule

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a cytoplasmic microtubule is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 trimethylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromere outer repeat regions does not occur.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 trimethylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in silent mating-type cassettes does not occur.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 trimethylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in silent mating-type cassettes occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abnormal histone methyltransferase activity (H3-K9 specific) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of H3-K9 specific histone methyltransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased histone methyltransferase activity (H3-K9 specific) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of H3-K9 specific histone methyltransferase activity is decreased.

label.value: abolished histone methyltransferase activity (H3-K9 specific) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which H3-K9 specific histone methyltransferase activity is absent.

label.value: decreased spatial extent of heterochromatin assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin is assembled over a smaller portion of the chromosome than normal.

label.value: abolished protein localization to heterochromatin at centromere outer repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to heterochromatin at centromere outer repeat regions does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein biotinylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the biotinylation of one or more specific proteins is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein biotinylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the biotinylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: aggregated filamentous actin in cytoplasm

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which filamentous actin (F-actin) is present in the cytoplasm in the form of dense, irregularly shaped aggregates.

label.value: increased actin cable assembly

value.value: A cytokinesis phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the assembly of actin cables is increased.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single cell division, multiseptate cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that undergoes a single round of cell division to produce daughter cells that have two or more septa apiece, which then die.

label.value: altered antisense RNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of antisense RNA measured in a cell differs from normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total antisense RNA or a specific antisense RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: altered level of translation gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more translation RNAs measured in a cell differs from normal (i.e. is higher or lower than observed in wild-type cells). Translation RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in translation.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: multiple Mei2 nuclear dots present in cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the cell contains two or more detectable Mei2 nuclear dot complexes instead of one.

label.value: Mei2 nuclear dot present in cell during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the cell contains a detectable Mei2 nuclear dot complex during the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Normally the Mei2 nuclear dot is only present during the meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: abolished CCR4-NOT complex binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which CCR4-NOT complex binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: abolished MTREC complex binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which MTREC complex binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: loss of punctate nuclear protein localization

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein that is normally localized to discrete regions in the nucleus, visible as foci or dots by microscopy, is abnormally localized such that dots cannot be observed.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 methylation at subtelomeric heterochromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in subtelomeric regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 methylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in silent mating-type cassettes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 methylation at rDNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at ribosomal DNA is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at rDNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at ribosomal DNA occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: increased mitotic recombination at rDNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of mitotic recombination is increased at ribosomal DNA.

label.value: inviable stubby multiseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is inviable and has one nucleus and more than one septum, and the cell diameter is larger than normal and the cell length is shorter than normal.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: incomplete septum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms a septum that does not completely bisect the cell.

label.value: thin, incomplete primary cell septum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms a primary septum that is thinner than normal and does not extend over the entire cell division site.

label.value: incomplete septum formed from asymmetrically located sites

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the septum is in two asymmetrically located parts and does not completely bisect the cell. Arises when septum assembly begins at two sites which are not on opposite sides of the medial cortex and terminates prematurely on both sides.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'abnormal contractile ring localization' (FYPO:0000033) because if the contractile ring forms in an abnormal location, the septum will also do so. The positions of both the contractile ring and the septum are determined by the processes that select the site of cell division.

label.value: increased secondary cell septum thickness

value.value: A septation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms a secondary septum that is thicker than normal.

label.value: decreased rate of medial membrane band assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of medial membrane band assembly is decreased. Medial membrane band assembly is the assembly of a sterol-rich region of the plasma membrane at the cell surface overlying the contractile ring.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for proline

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize proline, and therefore requires proline in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for tyrosine

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize tyrosine, and therefore requires tyrosine in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for glutamate

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize glutamate, and therefore requires glutamate in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: growth auxotrophic for tryptophan

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize tryptophan, and therefore requires tryptophan in the medium for vegetative cell growth.

label.value: C-shaped interphase microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form cytoplasmic microtubules that are curved to form a "C" shape, i.e. they follow a smooth bend rather than a straight line, with the curve centered at or near the midpoint of the microtubule, during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: long interphase microtubules curved around cell end

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form microtubules that are longer than normal and are curved, i.e. follow a smooth bend rather than a straight line, and extend around one or both ends of the cell, during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: ophthalmic acid absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of ophthalmic acid measured in a cell is too low to detect.

label.value: increased cellular gamma-glutamyl-2-aminobutyrate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of gamma-glutamyl-2-aminobutyrate (also called gamma-Glu-Abu) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: abolished anaerobic cell population growth

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow under anaerobic conditions.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow under anaerobic conditions, but does grow under aerobic or semi-aerobic conditions (a cell population that does not grow at any oxygen level would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.
